"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92647","Home Office","false","2014-10-22","<p>Operation Skybreaker is a pilot approach to encourage greater compliance with the Immigration rules in 10 pilot areas. Immigration Enforcement has used existing intelligence to prioritise its activities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92647/answer",,,,,,"2014-10-22T16:41:03.917339Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92647/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92647/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-10-10","Illegal Immigrants: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, under what criteria it was decided to deploy Operation Skybreaker in Brent, Ealing, Greenwich, Newham and Tower Hamlets; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","209310"
